1
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:50,880
=Dear Enemy=

2
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,460
Ms. Xu, how will you be heading back?

3
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,510
Want me to have the driver take you?

4
00:01:56,510 --> 00:01:58,133
Thank you, but I already called a ride.

5
00:01:58,340 --> 00:01:59,030
Luo Man.

6
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:00,510
Don't worry.

7
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:02,750
I'm a woman of my word.

8
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:04,590
I really liked that story of yours.

9
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:07,460
I read the whole thing in one sitting
after Mr. Zhou sent it to me.

10
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:10,510
Let's talk more next week.
Get into the details.

11
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:11,190
Sounds good.

12
00:02:11,390 --> 00:02:12,260
I'll call you.

13
00:02:13,230 --> 00:02:13,790
Watch out.

14
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:18,190
I've got to keep

15
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:19,540
our precious screenwriter safe.

16
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:21,700
Not to lie, Ms. Xu.

17
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:23,910
I've been following that story

18
00:02:23,910 --> 00:02:26,350
since the first page.

19
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:28,540
I like to think

20
00:02:28,670 --> 00:02:30,670
I've contributed a little.

21
00:02:30,670 --> 00:02:31,888
A huge contribution, actually.

22
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:33,470
Maybe when the credits roll,

23
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:34,790
I should get something like...

24
00:02:34,790 --> 00:02:36,190
Story consultant?

25
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:37,510
Original concept?

26
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:38,790
Mr. Zhou.

27
00:02:39,190 --> 00:02:41,950
Fund us and your name
can go anywhere you want.

28
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:42,510
Right?

29
00:02:42,510 --> 00:02:43,670
Sure. You're the boss.

30
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:46,470
My ride's here.

31
00:02:47,020 --> 00:02:48,190
Luo Man, it's a date.

32
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:48,977
See you next week.

33
00:02:49,070 --> 00:02:49,700
Bye-bye.

34
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:50,540
Take care.

35
00:02:50,540 --> 00:02:50,980
Bye.

36
00:02:55,860 --> 00:02:56,910
Ms. Xu's got

37
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:58,350
a sharp eye.

38
00:02:58,910 --> 00:02:59,980
That Chinese New Year hit?

39
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:02,630
She rescued it from a pile

40
00:03:02,630 --> 00:03:03,580
of rejected scripts.

41
00:03:03,860 --> 00:03:05,140
She's got a serious pull.

42
00:03:08,190 --> 00:03:09,070
Thanks again.

43
00:03:09,740 --> 00:03:10,910
Well, I should...

44
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:11,860
Would you like

45
00:03:12,350 --> 00:03:13,580
to take a walk?

46
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:17,790
I'm kind of tired,

47
00:03:18,790 --> 00:03:19,820
and I'm wearing heels.

48
00:03:20,510 --> 00:03:21,230
That's fine.

49
00:03:21,510 --> 00:03:22,470
I can

50
00:03:22,580 --> 00:03:23,260
carry you.

51
00:03:26,110 --> 00:03:26,860
Walking a bit

52
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:27,580
after drinking

53
00:03:27,580 --> 00:03:28,790
helps clear the head.

54
00:03:28,790 --> 00:03:29,470
Otherwise,

55
00:03:29,470 --> 00:03:31,466
you'll have a headache
when you get in the car.

56
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:33,390
Come on.

57
00:03:35,236 --> 00:03:40,020
(Life is bright. Flowers are lovely.
15 per bouquet.)

58
00:03:40,510 --> 00:03:40,910
Done.

59
00:03:41,230 --> 00:03:43,420
Here's to a lovely couple.

60
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:44,300
Thanks.

61
00:03:52,790 --> 00:03:53,420
Thank you.

62
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,790
Even the prices of flowers have gone up.

63
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,110
15 for a bouquet now.

64
00:04:29,740 --> 00:04:30,590
You've been

65
00:04:30,740 --> 00:04:31,910
rather quiet today.

66
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:34,710
Have I?

67
00:04:36,244 --> 00:04:37,540
I think I've been all right.

68
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:40,150
We're all familiar enough,

69
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:41,860
so no need to put on a show.

70
00:04:41,980 --> 00:04:43,590
No need for the cheeky banter either.

71
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:47,540
What's this?

72
00:04:48,110 --> 00:04:51,470
You can't even be bothered
to pretend anymore?

73
00:04:52,670 --> 00:04:53,910
So what?

74
00:04:53,910 --> 00:04:55,540
If there's no work excuse,

75
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:58,060
I can't even get you out for dinner?

76
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,500
Do you really think
I'm that calculating?

77
00:05:05,350 --> 00:05:06,940
Actually, yes, I am.

78
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:11,980
No need to be so brutally honest.

79
00:05:13,910 --> 00:05:14,740
Isn't honesty

80
00:05:15,740 --> 00:05:17,860
one of my better traits?

81
00:05:21,288 --> 00:05:23,270
What's wrong
with grabbing dinner with me?

82
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:24,860
Bad wine?

83
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:26,110
Bad food?

84
00:05:26,230 --> 00:05:27,030
Or am I just

85
00:05:27,110 --> 00:05:28,420
wasting your time?

86
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:31,860
What?

87
00:05:32,110 --> 00:05:34,540
Running low
on dining partners these days?

88
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:36,470
Can't be.

89
00:05:36,511 --> 00:05:38,500
At most, you're just short
one bickering partner.

90
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,670
Feeling lonely lately?

91
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:45,266
It's still more fun
hanging out with you.

92
00:05:48,022 --> 00:05:50,030
You've got plenty
of interesting people around.

93
00:05:50,030 --> 00:05:51,230
You don't need me.

94
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,060
But you're different.

95
00:05:56,110 --> 00:05:57,180
No, I'm not.

96
00:05:57,670 --> 00:05:58,670
We're all

97
00:05:58,860 --> 00:05:59,710
the same.

98
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:12,620
Hold this for me.

99
00:06:39,030 --> 00:06:39,710
I should...

100
00:06:39,710 --> 00:06:40,980
Would you like to come over

101
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:42,910
to my place?

102
00:06:48,620 --> 00:06:50,910
It's late. A man and a woman, alone...

103
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:52,620
It's not exactly appropriate.

104
00:06:56,670 --> 00:06:57,940
We never finished

105
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:00,940
that movie last time.

106
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:03,300
I'd like to finish it.

107
00:07:08,175 --> 00:07:11,960
=Episode 22=
(Oh, Women)

108
00:07:46,030 --> 00:07:47,060
Men really are

109
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:50,940
slower than women.

110
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:54,980
Sometimes,

111
00:07:55,860 --> 00:07:57,910
they lose things
without even realizing it.

112
00:08:00,740 --> 00:08:02,470
No clue what they've let slip away.

113
00:08:03,670 --> 00:08:05,790
And it always hits late.
Way, way after the fact.

114
00:08:11,540 --> 00:08:13,940
Isn't this kind of talk
a little inappropriate,

115
00:08:15,910 --> 00:08:17,380
given our current situation?

116
00:08:20,150 --> 00:08:21,540
I think it's perfectly appropriate.

117
00:08:22,590 --> 00:08:23,860
In fact,

118
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:25,300
I feel like now,

119
00:08:26,350 --> 00:08:27,670
we can actually be real.

120
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:29,590
Say what we actually mean.

121
00:08:34,140 --> 00:08:35,380
Have you ever held back?

122
00:08:39,111 --> 00:08:41,070
You've always just done
whatever you wanted.

123
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,380
As we get older,

124
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:53,260
people start

125
00:08:54,470 --> 00:08:55,780
to lose interest,

126
00:08:56,190 --> 00:08:58,830
in life and in everything.

127
00:09:00,190 --> 00:09:01,660
But even someone like that,

128
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,500
clumsy and unsure,

129
00:09:09,470 --> 00:09:11,260
he still once tried, really hard,

130
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:12,860
to prove to a woman

131
00:09:15,980 --> 00:09:17,500
that he still had some fire left

132
00:09:19,190 --> 00:09:20,140
for her.

133
00:09:34,550 --> 00:09:35,260
It's late.

134
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:42,070
I should go.

135
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:47,310
When I was one,

136
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:49,070
my parents got divorced.

137
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:52,830
They left me with my grandfather.

138
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:00,500
There were so many people in that house.

139
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,860
Siblings, cousins,

140
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:04,830
and a whole crowd.

141
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,020
Too many kids and too many mouths.

142
00:10:08,710 --> 00:10:09,380
I didn't even

143
00:10:10,230 --> 00:10:12,590
have my own bed growing up.

144
00:10:14,350 --> 00:10:16,020
Forget about having my own room.

145
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:23,190
My grandfather was good to me.

146
00:10:25,430 --> 00:10:26,550
But he was the strict,

147
00:10:27,110 --> 00:10:28,470
no-nonsense type.

148
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,830
I had to work so hard,

149
00:10:32,350 --> 00:10:33,950
and be the absolute best,

150
00:10:35,230 --> 00:10:37,070
just to get a rare smile of approval

151
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:39,020
from him.

152
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:42,430
That's when I started learning

153
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:44,710
how to read people.

154
00:10:46,430 --> 00:10:47,740
How to get along.

155
00:10:50,190 --> 00:10:51,660
And also, since then,

156
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,900
the only time I could truly relax

157
00:10:58,260 --> 00:11:00,500
was when I was alone, all by myself.

158
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:16,190
Intimacy has always been hard for me.

159
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:21,260
I've tried.

160
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:23,830
I've worked at it.

161
00:11:25,780 --> 00:11:26,740
I've failed.

162
00:11:31,950 --> 00:11:33,140
So,

163
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:35,550
Luo Man,

164
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:41,550
you're not the only one feeling lost.

165
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:24,660
Talk to me.

166
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:27,310
You didn't give it to him?

167
00:12:27,470 --> 00:12:28,860
What are you waiting for?

168
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:34,190
It doesn't matter if he wants it or not!

169
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:36,860
Chen Kaixi, listen to me.

170
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:39,500
Keeping the peace
doesn't always lead to peace.

171
00:12:39,710 --> 00:12:40,780
Let me be clear.

172
00:12:40,780 --> 00:12:42,070
You need to listen to me on this.

173
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:44,244
If not, you'll regret it
for the rest of your life!

174
00:12:45,980 --> 00:12:47,110
All right.

175
00:12:47,430 --> 00:12:49,230
Okay. Sure. Whatever.

176
00:13:15,380 --> 00:13:15,950
Thanks.

177
00:13:20,044 --> 00:13:21,230
Everything all right?

178
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:24,550
I just don't get it.

179
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:27,430
What's the point of marriage?

180
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:29,620
How can there be no bottom line?

181
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:35,740
If you ask me,

182
00:13:36,980 --> 00:13:38,140
I think

183
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:40,740
you should try not to get
too involved in their mess.

184
00:13:41,230 --> 00:13:41,950
Why not?

185
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:44,650
At the end of the day,
they're still husband and wife.

186
00:13:45,310 --> 00:13:46,140
They're family.

187
00:13:46,470 --> 00:13:48,140
And sometimes,

188
00:13:48,780 --> 00:13:50,830
there is no bottom line with family.

189
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:53,230
So what,

190
00:13:54,177 --> 00:13:55,740
you just keep swallowing it down?

191
00:13:55,822 --> 00:13:57,380
Pretend nothing's wrong and carry on?

192
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:00,500
Couples fight, sure.

193
00:14:00,860 --> 00:14:02,310
But they also make up.

194
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:04,660
Think about it.

195
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,230
After all these years,

196
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:08,590
do you think
Chen Kaixi can live without Chen Mian?

197
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:11,550
Her dependency on him

198
00:14:12,070 --> 00:14:13,860
might not just be financial.

199
00:14:14,190 --> 00:14:15,430
It could be

200
00:14:15,430 --> 00:14:16,430
emotional too.

201
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:18,260
So...

202
00:14:18,710 --> 00:14:19,260
Just

203
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:20,380
be careful.

204
00:14:20,380 --> 00:14:22,350
Don't get caught in the crossfire.

205
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:24,710
Why the scoff?

206
00:14:26,244 --> 00:14:27,900
I suppose, if anyone knows
about divorce,

207
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,310
it's you.

208
00:14:29,311 --> 00:14:30,622
You're speaking from experience.

209
00:14:38,380 --> 00:14:39,830
You know,

210
00:14:40,110 --> 00:14:41,500
I often

211
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:44,830
find myself admiring,

212
00:14:44,830 --> 00:14:46,110
maybe even envying,

213
00:14:47,020 --> 00:14:47,830
that fire

214
00:14:48,350 --> 00:14:49,260
in you.

215
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:52,070
That anger,

216
00:14:52,660 --> 00:14:53,590
and passion for life.

217
00:15:00,620 --> 00:15:01,620
Can you

218
00:15:02,070 --> 00:15:02,860
turn around?

219
00:15:05,660 --> 00:15:06,710
Just turn around.

220
00:15:19,430 --> 00:15:21,310
When I first saw it,

221
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:23,190
I thought it suited you perfectly.

222
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:26,230
So, I bought it.

223
00:15:35,310 --> 00:15:37,190
I do not think it suits me.

224
00:15:57,780 --> 00:15:59,140
I do not

225
00:16:02,470 --> 00:16:03,900
like wearing necklaces.

226
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:18,470
But thank you.

227
00:17:04,861 --> 00:17:10,140
(LEGEND Jeux De Liens Collection)

228
00:17:14,461 --> 00:17:16,380
(Natural diamond, ruby, 15,600.00)

229
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,940
I am still not realistic enough.

230
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:37,540
(Yancheng Zuanshi International School)

231
00:17:41,323 --> 00:17:42,580
(Divorce Agreement)

232
00:17:57,824 --> 00:18:00,110
(Teacher Notes,
Parent Feedback, Certificates)

233
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:09,940
Let's go, Tiao.

234
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:20,550
Tiao, why are you not moving?

235
00:18:21,220 --> 00:18:22,420
We're going to be late.

236
00:18:22,420 --> 00:18:24,700
We wouldn't want to leave
a bad impression on the teacher.

237
00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:26,030
Mommy,

238
00:18:26,550 --> 00:18:28,860
will it just be you with me from now on?

239
00:18:37,790 --> 00:18:39,550
I will always be with you, all right?

240
00:18:48,180 --> 00:18:49,310
Daddy! Over here!

241
00:18:49,310 --> 00:18:50,030
Hurry up!

242
00:19:03,070 --> 00:19:03,940
Honey.

243
00:19:04,241 --> 00:19:04,940
Let's go.

244
00:19:09,577 --> 00:19:11,109
Mr. Chen and Mrs. Chen.

245
00:19:11,110 --> 00:19:12,355
Would you like anything to drink?

246
00:19:12,355 --> 00:19:13,644
This will take a while.

247
00:19:14,270 --> 00:19:15,350
Coffee, please. Thanks.

248
00:19:15,350 --> 00:19:15,830
All right.

249
00:19:15,830 --> 00:19:16,830
Nothing for me. Thank you.

250
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:17,380
All right.

251
00:19:17,460 --> 00:19:18,180
Hello.

252
00:19:18,990 --> 00:19:20,140
Hi, Johnny.

253
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:21,220
My name is Lisa,

254
00:19:21,220 --> 00:19:24,022
and I'm here to give you a school tour.
Do you want to go with me?

255
00:19:24,110 --> 00:19:24,990
Let's go.

256
00:19:25,550 --> 00:19:26,420
Have fun!

257
00:19:33,227 --> 00:19:35,400
(Honorary Credential, Chen Zhi,
Excellent Young Role Model)

258
00:19:35,688 --> 00:19:37,330
(Certificate,
Chen Zhi, Perfect Attendance)

259
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:41,460
I see here that Tiao

260
00:19:41,460 --> 00:19:43,420
attended kindergarten at Qiaowei.

261
00:19:43,710 --> 00:19:46,000
And it looks like you traveled
to quite a few places together

262
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:46,750
during the holidays.

263
00:19:46,755 --> 00:19:47,622
Yes, that is right.

264
00:19:47,790 --> 00:19:49,350
Why did you not consider

265
00:19:49,460 --> 00:19:51,310
sending Tiao to Qiaowei Elementary?

266
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:53,110
What made you choose Zuanshi?

267
00:19:53,288 --> 00:19:54,488
We chose Zuanshi

268
00:19:54,511 --> 00:19:56,940
because we believe
in the school's educational philosophy.

269
00:19:56,940 --> 00:19:58,750
Education is not just
about taking exams.

270
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,110
It is about guiding children

271
00:20:00,110 --> 00:20:02,800
to explore their relationship
with themselves and with the world.

272
00:20:03,380 --> 00:20:05,590
It sounds like
you have done your homework.

273
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:08,940
When it comes
to your child's growth and education,

274
00:20:08,940 --> 00:20:10,590
what matters most to you?

275
00:20:11,750 --> 00:20:12,940
We hope he can develop

276
00:20:12,940 --> 00:20:14,420
a global perspective

277
00:20:14,420 --> 00:20:15,620
and the capabilities to match.

278
00:20:15,940 --> 00:20:18,750
Zuanshi offers
a multilingual curriculum.

279
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:20,790
We are very optimistic

280
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:22,070
about this approach to education.

281
00:20:29,460 --> 00:20:30,860
What my wife said is quite right.

282
00:20:31,110 --> 00:20:32,830
But actually, we value

283
00:20:32,830 --> 00:20:34,420
our child's self-motivation

284
00:20:34,790 --> 00:20:36,460
and independence even more.

285
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:39,030
We believe that every child

286
00:20:39,620 --> 00:20:40,660
has unique strengths.

287
00:20:41,180 --> 00:20:43,030
If you let them grow freely,

288
00:20:43,030 --> 00:20:45,830
they will eventually shine
in their own way.

